.TH WRITEBETTERER 1 "February 2026" "writebetterer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
writebetterer \- rewrite or query text using an LLM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B writebetterer
[\fB\-mode\fR \fItype\fR]
[\fB\-model\fR \fIname\fR]
[\fB\-provider\fR \fIname\fR]
[\fB\-prompt\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B writebetterer
reads text from standard input, sends it to an LLM, and writes the result to
standard output.
.PP
By default it classifies the input as code, configuration, or prose, then
rewrites it with appropriate improvements. With the \fB\-prompt\fR flag it
instead sends the input as a direct query and returns the LLM's response.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-mode " \fItype\fR"
Content type for rewriting: \fBauto\fR (default), \fBcode\fR, \fBconfig\fR,
or \fBprose\fR. In \fBauto\fR mode the input is classified automatically.
Ignored when \fB\-prompt\fR is set.
.TP
.BR \-model " \fIname\fR"
Override the default model selection. When omitted, a model is chosen based on
the provider and content type.
.TP
.BR \-provider " \fIname\fR"
LLM provider: \fBgemini\fR or \fBclaude\fR. Defaults to the
\fBWRITEBETTERER_PROVIDER\fR environment variable, then \fBgemini\fR.
.TP
.B \-prompt
Send the input as a direct prompt to the LLM, bypassing classification and
rewriting. Useful for general\-purpose queries.
.TP
.B \-v
Print provider, mode, and model information to standard error.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B WRITEBETTERER_PROVIDER
Default LLM provider (\fBgemini\fR or \fBclaude\fR). Overridden by
\fB\-provider\fR.
.TP
.B GEMINI_API_KEY
API key for the Gemini provider. May be a literal key or an \fBop://\fR
reference for 1Password lookup.
.TP
.B ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
API key for the Claude provider. May be a literal key or an \fBop://\fR
reference for 1Password lookup.
.SH EXAMPLES
Rewrite prose with automatic detection:
.PP
.RS
echo "Hello wrold, how are you todya?" | writebetterer
.RE
.PP
Rewrite code explicitly:
.PP
.RS
cat main.go | writebetterer \-mode code \-provider claude
.RE
.PP
Ask a question directly:
.PP
.RS
echo "What is the capital of France?" | writebetterer \-prompt
.RE
.PP
Verbose output:
.PP
.RS
echo "Fix this sentense." | writebetterer \-v
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (empty input, invalid flags, API failure).
